  "notes": "Sir James Taylor — a knight. Born 1550 in London. Resided in Prestbury, Cheshire. Daughter: Cecelia Taylor (1580-1662, born in London), who married Sir Robert Rogers. Cecelia eventually emigrated to colonial Massachusetts, dying in Watertown in 1662. Died 1627 at age 77. Buried January 7, 1627 at Dalton-In-Furness, Lancashire. Two knights in this line — Sir James and his son-in-law Sir Robert Rogers."
